Although I am not a rogue by trade I do frequent The Safehouse brushing up on what skills we do share. I came across this quest and since everyone knows if you have a question you come here...I came here. Summary: Npc in Firiona Vie wants you to locate Al'Kabor's research notes for her and give them to another NPC in FV.<br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:35:33 2001] Your Location is -3146.10, 2659.47, -77.47<br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:35:35 2001] You say, 'Hail, Realla Segoan'<br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:35:35 2001] Realla Segoan says 'Greetings, Keerin . I am Realla Segoan from the city of Erudin.  I cannot spend time chatting with you now. I have [official tasks] to perform. <br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:35:42 2001] You say, 'what official tasks'<br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:35:42 2001] Realla Segoan says 'I have been sent to this continent by the High Council of Erudin to find information about the disappearance of [Al'Kabor]. <br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:35:50 2001] You say, 'what about Al'Kabor'<br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:35:51 2001] Realla Segoan says 'Al'Kabor is believed to be the most powerful living wizard on Norrath.  In addition, he is also one of Erudin's oldest citizens.  The High Council is very interested in receiving information about his disappearance.  So far, from the [reports] that I have collected, there appears to have been a [troublemaking gnome] involved. <br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:35:54 2001] You say, 'what reports'<br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:35:55 2001] Realla Segoan says 'I have received many reports regarding the disappearance.  Adventurers upon this continent have reported sightings of some of Al'Kabor's [missing research notes]. <br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:36:00 2001] You say, 'what troublemaking gnome'<br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:36:01 2001] Realla Segoan says 'Yes, a gnome.  I have received reports that the gnomish wizard, Ognit Eznertob, was near Al'Kabor when he disappeared.  I have attempted to contact him about it, however, he seems to be avoiding me and the city of Erudin.  This is not the first time that this gnome has caused trouble for the Erudites.  He was arrested a while back for tampering with hatch in the Hole, releasing evil denizens from the Underfoot.  If he is responsible for the disappearance, great lengths will be taken to assure the citizens of Erudin that the gnome will no longer be trouble for them. <br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:36:11 2001] You say, 'what missing research notes'<br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:36:12 2001] Realla Segoan says 'It appears that through his travels, the great wizard has misplaced some of his research notes.  Perhaps if I can find someone to [help collect the research notes], the High Council may be able to determine what caused Al'Kabor's disappearance.  However, only those who truly know the path the great wizard's research has taken him will know where to find the missing research notes. <br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:36:25 2001] You say, 'I will help collect the research notes'<br>
<br>
[Sat Nov 17 02:36:25 2001] Realla Segoan says 'Excellent!  Take this Research Binder and fill it with the research notes when you find them.  Once it is filled, seal it and take it to Noilgin Mindtune here at the outpost, so that he may deliver it to Erudin. Be forewarned though, it will be a dangerous path to follow. Most likely, the research notes have fallen into possession of some very dangerous beings. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  She hands you a research binder with six slots...Noilgin Mindtune is located on the docks </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Al'Kabor had this to say about his journals &quot;I recently discovered that during brief moments of excitement in my travels, I unknowingly left behind research notes in some of the areas I ventured into. It is of no concern to me, though. For years, I have been surrounded by foolish ones that could not fully understand the effectiveness of the spells I have created. Why should I now expect one of those inept troglodytes to discover the vastness of my research of the Combine Empire? The journals of the Combine Empire require purely scientific minds--not unlike my own--to decipher.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> his journals are found at the everquest.com page looks like he has been to Dreadlands, Burning Woods, Kaesora, Chardok, Firiona Vie, Kedge Keep, the Hole, Skyfire, Western Wastes, Greadt Divide, Karanas, and probably where the spires/quadroliths are...heh like this narrows it down any =P</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Anyone received any of his notes yet? Thanks in advance for your help. I will zip around Norrath and will post more as I learn more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/17/01 3:00:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Al'Kabor's Research notes</span><hr size=1> Funny, I checked her out 10 mins ago before I logged.  She hands you the Binder, which is 6 slot and holds Tiny (fyi). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usoulstoneelwyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soulstone Elwyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/17/01 4:46:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Al'Kabor's Research notes</span><hr size=1> I got a gm quest through him and Makil Rargon from the fussibility quest.  Makil was at dl spires and told me to go find Al'Kabor in burning woods (well he really gave the quest to the cleric who showed up after I started talking to him cause he said he didn't trust rogues). He talked about how some experiment confirmed his fears about the Combine empire gave the cleric a bag of the tinkerers and we all got nice (but not uber) earings or rings as a result.  Dunno if that has anything to do with your quest but we'll see I guess.<br>
<br>
Soulstone 52 rogue <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urediofqeynos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redi of Qeynos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/17/01 10:56:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Al'Kabor's Research notes</span><hr size=1> I'm trying to look into this as well, though we don't have any solid leads.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Most likely, the research notes have fallen into possession of some very dangerous beings.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
To me, this sounds like it's boss-type mobs who have the journal pages... maybe the Sathirs and such. That would limit the quest doing (especially since this can't be multied), but hopefully imply that the reward is something pretty nice. 'course, that's all conjecture at this point.<br>
<br>
Based on what I read about the recent Al'Kabor event (and the current timeline), I'd imagine that this is Al working on his ports to the Nexus of Luclin.<br>
<br>
I checked NK gypsies and Temple of Sol Ro wizzies with no luck, BTW.<br>
<br>
hrmm... I wonder if the quest team keeps the same roles through different events - i.e. the guy who plays Al'Kabor is always the guy who plays him. That'd be interesting, as he and I had something of a... disagreement last time we met. Always funny to get booted to Iceclad docks from GD (come to think of it, he prolly used the effect on me that the gnome in NRo now uses to send you to iceclad), talk to a Guide you kinda know, and get ported back into the event <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
-Redi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unaeltp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>naelTP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 1:34:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Al'Kabor's Research notes</span><hr size=1> I was camping Xalgoz(sp) in Kasorea, killing the spawns around his room so I could pull him, a no drop Research Notes part 2 dropped.  I was there for two 8 hour days and only seen this drop once.  Perhaps this is part of the same quest no?  I destroyed the note.<br>
<br>
Also, this come off random trash spawns around Xalgoz(sp) not xalgoz himself. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unaeltp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>naelTP</A> at: 11/18/01 1:36:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukeerinskedaddle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keerin Skedaddle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 2:37:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Al'Kabor's Research notes</span><hr size=1> Found page 6 of the research notes in Dreadland's Combine City. Off a plaguebone thief, blue to 51...hit hard but died fast. 4 spawn inside one of the pyramids. There was a wizard who killed about 20 for exp and saw no note. I killed 4 and saw it on my fourth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unitanita.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NitaNita</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 6:01:39 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Al'Kabor's Research notes</span><hr size=1> I found parts 2 AND 3 in Kaesora, in the library area. So they seem to be random drops around the zone. Part 6 can indeed drop in the dreadlands, while I didn't see that one myself, there were some /oocs about it when one dropped there yesterday.<br>
<br>
Amanita <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unalanie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nalanie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 8:03:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Al'Kabor's Research notes</span><hr size=1> There is a thread on this one at Graffe's.<br>
